# ğŸ Conda Setup Guide for RTX 5090

Your professor is right. The system-level Python might be too old or broken for the 5090. **Conda** is the industry standard because it installs its own safe CUDA libraries.

**Follow these steps on the server:**

### 1. Install Miniconda (Small version of Anaconda)
```bash
# Download installer
wget https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh

# Run installer (Type 'yes' to license and 'yes' to init)
bash Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh

'''
# Try initializing specifically
~/miniconda3/bin/conda init bash
# OR if that folder doesn't exist, try:
~/anaconda3/bin/conda init bash

# Refresh terminal to make 'conda' command work
source ~/.bashrc
```



### 2. Create a Clean Environment
We will use Python 3.11 (modern & stable).
```bash
conda create -n dbrouting python=3.11 -y
conda activate dbrouting
```

### 3. Install CUDA Toolkit & PyTorch Nightly ğŸ› ï¸
This is the magic part. Conda will ensure the drivers match.
```bash
# 1. Install NVIDIA CUDA Toolkit 12.4+ (required for 5090) from nvidia channel
conda install -c nvidia cuda-toolkit -y

# 2. Install PyTorch Nightly (CUDA 12.6 support)
pip install --pre torch torchvision torchaudio --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/nightly/cu126
```

### 4. Install Other Dependencies
```bash
pip install transformers accelerate bitsandbytes scikit-learn pandas numpy google-generativeai tqdm sentence-transformers einops python-dotenv
```

